<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Macrocnemic zoantharians with a simple mesogleal muscle (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ode.2008.10.003" author="Sinniger, F" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="B268" refString="Sinniger, F, Haeussermann, V, 2009. Zoanthids (Cnidaria: Hexacorallia: Zoantharia) from shallow waters of the southern Chilean fjord region, with descriptions of a new genus and two new species. Organisms Diversity &amp; Evolution 9(1): 23-36. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ode.2008.10.003" title="Zoanthids (Cnidaria: Hexacorallia: Zoantharia) from shallow waters of the southern Chilean fjord region, with descriptions of a new genus and two new species. Organisms Diversity &amp; Evolution 9 (1): 23 - 36." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ode.2008.10.003" year="2009">
Sinniger and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Häussermann">Haeussermann</normalizedToken>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
: 26).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
The family-group 
<taxonomicName class="Anthozoa" family="Epizoanthidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Zoantharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Epizoanthidae</taxonomicName>
(as &quot; 
<taxonomicName family="Epizoanthidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Zoantharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Epizoanthinae">Epizoanthinae</taxonomicName>
&quot;) was established by 
<bibRefCitation author="Delage, Y" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refId="B67" refString="Delage, Y, Herouard, E, 1901. Zoanthides. - Zoanthidae. pp. 654-667, pls. 65. In: Traite de Zoologie concrete. Tome II - 2me Partie. Les Coelenteres. C. Reinwald, Paris, x + [xi] + 848 pp., pls. 1-72. [&lt; 15 Nov 1901 (Friedlaender 1901: 579)]" title="Zoanthides. - Zoanthidae. pp. 654 - 667, pls. 65. In: Traite de Zoologie concrete. Tome II - 2 me Partie. Les Coelenteres. C. Reinwald, Paris, x + [xi] + 848 pp., pls. 1 - 72. [&lt;15 Nov 1901 (Friedlaender 1901: 579)]" year="1901">
Delage and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hérouard">Herouard</normalizedToken>
(1901
</bibRefCitation>
: 664, 665) as monotypic, with the inclusion of only the type genus. Three genera are currently assigned to 
<taxonomicName class="Anthozoa" family="Epizoanthidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Zoantharia" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Epizoanthidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Recent molecular and morphological studies (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1186/s12862-015-0406-1" author="Swain, TD" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="B284" refString="Swain, TD, Schellinger, JL, Strimaitis, AM, Reuter, KE, 2015. Evolution of anthozoan polyp retraction mechanisms: convergent functional morphology and evolutionary allometry of the marginal musculature in order Zoanthidea (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Hexacorallia). BMC Evolutionary Biology 15(123): 1-19. https://doi.org/10.1186/s12862-015-0406-1" title="Evolution of anthozoan polyp retraction mechanisms: convergent functional morphology and evolutionary allometry of the marginal musculature in order Zoanthidea (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Hexacorallia). BMC Evolutionary Biology 15 (123): 1 - 19." url="https://doi.org/10.1186/s12862-015-0406-1" year="2015">Swain et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
) suggest that this diagnosis should be revised following a complete revision of the suborder. Currently, molecular signatures such as those suggested in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2108/zsj.25.1253" author="Sinniger, F" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refId="B270" refString="Sinniger, F, Reimer, JD, Pawlowski, J, 2008. Potential of DNA sequences to identify zoanthids (Cnidaria:Zoantharia). Zoological Science 25: 1253-1260. https://doi.org/10.2108/zsj.25.1253" title="Potential of DNA sequences to identify zoanthids (Cnidaria: Zoantharia). Zoological Science 25: 1253 - 1260." url="https://doi.org/10.2108/zsj.25.1253" year="2008">Sinniger et al. (2008)</bibRefCitation>
and in 
<bibRefCitation author="Sinniger, F" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="B273" refString="Sinniger, F, Ocana, OV, Baco, AR, 2013. Diversity of zoanthids (Anthozoa: Hexacorallia) on Hawaiian seamounts: description of the Hawaiian gold coral and additional zoanthids. PLoS ONE 8(1): e52607 (pp. [1]-[13]). [9 Jan 2013 (p. [1])]" title="Diversity of zoanthids (Anthozoa: Hexacorallia) on Hawaiian seamounts: description of the Hawaiian gold coral and additional zoanthids. PLoS ONE 8 (1): e 52607 (pp. [1] - [13]). [9 Jan 2013 (p. [1])]" year="2013">Sinniger et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
appear efficient to distinguish macrocnemic genera.
</paragraph>
